						               													<description>Released in 2009, by the French fantasy miniatures company 'Taban Miniatures', EDEN is a skirmishes game, played with 32mm scale miniatures.&amp;#10;That product is edited in English, Spanish, German and&amp;#10;French.&amp;#10;It is also available for free downloading in Hungarian, Brazilian and italian and soon in Italian.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Eden is aimed at an adult audience. It features easy-to-learn rules and a very addictive system.&amp;#10;The flexibility of the game allows players to adapt the strategic level to their own taste and to live fast and exciting combats.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game Features&amp;#10;- A real skirmish game, fast-paced, bloody and tactical.&amp;#10;- Compact format : 3-6 miniatures per player, one-hour games on a 2&amp;rsquo;x2&amp;rsquo; battlefield.&amp;#10;- A system of different missions for each player, making every single match a new experience.&amp;#10;- Open army lists with the possibility to create unusual compositions and nine resulting gameplay experiences.&amp;#10;- Short rules, easy to learn but hard to master.&amp;#10;- Tactical cards, influencing the action every turn and establishing a strategy before the battle via a deck building system.&amp;#10;- Wounds location affecting the fighters&amp;rsquo; performances.&amp;#10;- Top quality pewter miniatures, sculpted by awards winning artists.&amp;#10;- An original background, mysterious yet classic.&amp;#10;- Optional rules taking into account all the parameters of a real battle (weather, scenery, unpredictable events, wild beasts, etc).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Core rule system by Pierre &amp;quot;Jugger&amp;quot; Joanne, upon an original idea of Mohamed &amp;quot;Mohand&amp;quot; Ait Mehdi.&amp;#10;Game Design team : P. Joanne, Frederic &amp;quot;Berf&amp;quot; Maendly, M. Ait Mehdi and Emmanuel &amp;quot;Sered&amp;quot; Krebbs.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
